00044 #define MINAPI_PLUGIN_CALL(fname,fcall) \
00045         do { \
00046                 DLListIterator it = dl_list_head(get_plugin_list()); \
00047                 while (it!=DLListNULLIterator) { \
00048                         if ( ((eapiIn_t*)dl_list_data(it))->fname ) { \
00049                                 ((eapiIn_t*)dl_list_data(it))->fcall; \
00050                         } \
00051                         it = dl_list_next(it); \
00052                 } \
00053         } while(0);

00146 typedef struct {

00148         ** Adds a new test module to MIN. Engine calls new_module() if the

00154 
00155         /* --------------------------------------------------------------------
00156         ** Adds a test case file to the test module identified by moduleid. 
00157         ** Note: This must be called at least once for every module added(
00158         ** with add_test_module()), with the testcasefile parameter as "\0". So
00159         ** that engine knows not to expect any more files. 
00160         ** returns 0 if the async operation was started succesfully
00161         **         1 in case of error
00162         */
00163         int (*add_test_case_file) (unsigned moduleid, char *testcasefile);
00164 
00165         /* --------------------------------------------------------------------
00166         ** Signals engine to start executing test case with caseid from module 
00167         ** with moduleid. If the groupid is non-zero test case is started when
00168         ** there are no cases running with the same groupid. (sequential
00169         ** execution)
00170         ** returns 0 if the async operation was started succesfully
00171         **         1 in case of error
00172         */
00173         int (*start_case) (unsigned moduleid, unsigned caseid, 
00174                            unsigned groupid);

00189         /* --------------------------------------------------------------------
00190         ** Abort test case
